headlines.description: — The Toronto Raptors keep on rolling, and the Charlotte Hornets keep on floundering.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam, Raptors beat Hornets 116-101 for 6th straight win

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 21 points and Jimmy Butler had 19 as the Eastern Conference-leading Miami Heat cruised to a 121-100 win over the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo, Butler lead Heat to 121-100 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Devin Booker got off to a big start while helping Phoenix build a huge lead. The NBA-leading Suns remained in control the rest of the way and came away with yet another win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 38, NBA-best Suns hang on, beat Bulls 127-124

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson is finding his groove.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson's 21 points, late 3s lead Warriors past Thunder

events.name: New York Knicks at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 32 points, seven rebounds, and six assists to lead the Utah Jazz to a 113-104 victory over the New York Knicks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell nets 32, rallies Jazz past Knicks for 3rd straight
